Name: ciliary body spindle cell melanoma
Definition: A ciliary body cancer that is located_in the ciliary body and composed of spindled neoplastic cells arranged in sheets and fascicles.
Synonym: spindle cell melanoma of the Ciliary body

Name: obsolete AIDS retinopathy
Definition: A Human immunodeficiency virus infectious disease that results_in microvascular changes located_in retina
Synonym: spindle cell melanoma of the Ciliary body

Name: malignant ciliary body melanoma
Definition: A Bartholin's gland benign neoplasm that has_material_basis_in gland and muscle components.
